Hi, I'm Chris. 







Today we're going to look at how to politely disagree during a group discussion 







I think that young people in Hong Kong should also be given six thousand dollars each 







Actually I'm afraid  I don't agree with you 







I feel that if young people were given six thousand dollars 







perhaps the government would have a lot less money 







When you want to disagree with someone, It's good to be firm and polite 







Instead of saying 'in my opinion', you could say I'm afraid I disagree with you 







So, it is important that the money should be spent on health care, because… 







Sorry, can I just stop you for a moment? 







I'd like to add something to that. Sure. 







It's okay to interrupt someone when necessary 







Here's some phrases you can use 







